  "body": "Some pain points of git flow that we are encountering:\r\n\r\n- merge conflicts bringing stable into unstable\r\n- merge squash vs regular merge, clicking the wrong button on Github\r\n\r\nBoth of this issues would not happen if we do a code freeze during beta testing. However we won't be able to\r\n- Merge feature branches during beta testing\r\n- Do parallel releases (minor + patch)\r\n- Do hot-fixes on top of stable (check if this is correct)\r\n\r\nWe should try this for v0.41.0 or v0.42.0 to check how the pros vs cons feel",
